==Japanese==
'''失礼''' ([[しつれい]], ''shitsurei'')

===Quasi-Adjective===
失礼な (しつれいな, ''shitsurei na'')

#rude, impolite
#*失礼な人 ''shitsurei na hito'' - a rude person
#*そういう言い方は失礼だ。 ''Sō iu iikata wa shitsurei da.'' - It's impolite to say it like that.
#*失礼ですが ''shitsurei desu ga'' - I don't mean to be rude, but...

===Verb===
失礼する (しつれいする, ''shitsurei suru'')
#to be rude
#*失礼しました。 ''Shitsurei shimashita.'' - I'm sorry. (lit. I was rude.)
#to leave when others remain (which is considered impolite)
#*お先に失礼します。 ''O-saki ni shitsurei shimasu.'' - I'm leaving now. (lit. I will be rude [and leave] before you.)

